---
// src/pages/index.astro
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout door="home">

  <!-- ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="page-body">
    <section class="hero" aria-label="Introduction">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Skinny Union Project</p>
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        Professional workers who want higher wages have never had a union
        <em>designed for them.</em>
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-rule"></div>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The skinny union is the collective bargaining model built for people who already know they're
        worth more — and don't need a grievance apparatus to prove it.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Three Doors ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="page-body">
    <nav class="door-grid" aria-label="Site sections">

      <a href="/employees" class="door-card door-card--employees">
        <span class="door-tag">Employees</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"Get Paid"</span>
        <span class="door-register">Activation register</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          You know what the market pays for your work. Your employer is counting on you not to
          do anything about it. Here's what collective bargaining looks like when the only agenda
          is compensation.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/research" class="door-card door-card--research">
        <span class="door-tag">Research</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"Ooh, a White Paper!"</span>
        <span class="door-register">Sober register</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          The legal architecture is sound. The labor market analysis is documented. The
          objections are addressed head-on. Everything is already here.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/press" class="door-card door-card--press">
        <span class="door-tag">Press</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"The Missing Story"</span>
        <span class="door-register">Sober register</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          The professional labor market has a structural compensation problem that collective
          bargaining theory predicts and empirical evidence confirms. The skinny union is the
          mechanism that solves it. The story hasn't been told yet.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

    </nav>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
